            <h1 align="left" float="top" style="font-family:&quot;Helvetica&quot;">UNC to Honor Stuart Scott</h1>
            <div _rdeditor_temp="1">
            <div style="font-family: Verdana; font-size: 13.3333px;"><span style="font-size: 13px;">The UNC School of Media and Journalism will honor iconic ESPN anchor and UNC alumnus Stuart Scott at an Oct. 23, 2015, induction ceremony into the N.C. Journalism Hall of Fame.</span></div>
            <div style="font-family: Verdana; font-size: 13.3333px;"><span style="font-size: 13px;">Tickets to the event &mdash; which will feature remarks from Chancellor Carol Folt, Dean Susan King, soccer legend Mia Hamm and "Voice of the Tar Heels" Jones Angell &mdash; are $75. The deadline to register Oct. 13.</span></div>
            <div style="font-family: Verdana; font-size: 13.3333px;"><span style="font-size: 13px;">Gifts commemorating Stuart's induction into the N.C. Journalism Hall of Fame will help the UNC School of Media and Journalism honor and continue his legacy at the University he loved and with students he inspired and mentored throughout his career.</span></div>
            <div style="font-family: Verdana; font-size: 13.3333px;"><span style="font-size: 13px;">A special thank you to Capitol Broadcasting, the parent company to WRAL-TV where Scott worked in one of his first broadcast jobs, for underwriting the event.</span></div>
            <br>
            </div>
            <a href="http://mj.unc.edu/news/stuart-scott-be-inducted-nc-journalism-hall-fame-oct-23-tickets-available" class="read-more" style="color: rgb(240,91,120); text-decoration: none;" target="_blank"><strong>READ MORE</strong></a>
            </td>
